it's, it's me.


987
01:02:54.918 --> 01:02:59.513
Call me when you get this.
We need to talk.


988
01:03:13.537 --> 01:03:14.699
Catherine!

989
01:03:15.935 --> 01:03:17.398
You're here!

990
01:03:17.400 --> 01:03:18.565
Well, we're getting married
in a couple of days.


991
01:03:18.567 --> 01:03:21.331
I thought it was time
I reclaim my cowboy.


992
01:03:24.461 --> 01:03:26.560
Let me get your bags.

993
01:03:28.459 --> 01:03:29.889
All right.

994
01:03:29.891 --> 01:03:31.955
I thought you were
selling this place.


995
01:03:31.957 --> 01:03:34.752
Wasn't that whole reason
of coming here?


996
01:03:34.754 --> 01:03:40.014
Well, I was, but then I got here, and
realized maybe I should hold onto it.


997
01:03:40.016 --> 01:03:42.147
Why?

998
01:03:42.149 --> 01:03:44.645
Well, I grew up here.
This is my home.


999
01:03:45.745 --> 01:03:47.476
Listen, I'm so glad you're here.

1000
01:03:47.478 --> 01:03:50.707
I've learned so much about myself
over the last couple of weeks.


1001
01:03:50.709 --> 01:03:52.939
What are you wearing?

1002
01:03:52.941 --> 01:03:57.468
- Just some old clothes. Work clothes.
- Work?


1003
01:03:57.470 --> 01:04:00.799
Look, I thought we could keep
this house as a home base


1004
01:04:00.801 --> 01:04:02.364
for when we're not working.

1005
01:04:02.366 --> 01:04:03.697
Then we could spend time
here with our children.


1006
01:04:03.699 --> 01:04:06.195
Teach them how to fish
and ride horses.


1007
01:04:06.197 --> 01:04:08.892
Give them something real,
something out of the spotlight.


1008
01:04:09.929 --> 01:04:11.726
Our... our children?

1009
01:04:11.728 --> 01:04:14.422
You want to have children,
don't you?


1010
01:04:14.424 --> 01:04:16.487
I mean, I know we never
discussed it, but...


1011
01:04:16.489 --> 01:04:19.385
We love each other
and we're getting married.


1012
01:04:19.387 --> 01:04:23.061
We have a lifetime to learn everything
we need to know about each other.


1013
01:04:27.880 --> 01:04:29.478
I want what you want.

1014
01:04:29.480 --> 01:04:32.274
So, why don't I get changed,

1015
01:04:32.276 --> 01:04:35.273
and you can make
reservations someplace nice,


1016
01:04:35.275 --> 01:04:39.104
and we'll go out
on the town and celebrate.


1017
01:04:39.106 --> 01:04:40.736
Well, there's a diner in town,

1018
01:04:40.738 --> 01:04:42.735
but there aren't any fancy
restaurants close by.


1019
01:04:42.737 --> 01:04:47.831
- Where do people eat?
- At home. They cook.


1020
01:04:49.531 --> 01:04:51.361
Look...

1021
01:04:51.363 --> 01:04:53.226
It's gonna be great, all right?

1022
01:04:53.228 --> 01:04:54.458
We're gonna get up early
tomorrow morning,


1023
01:04:54.460 --> 01:04:57.823
I'm gonna take you on that hike,
then we can go fishin'.


1024
01:04:57.825 --> 01:05:00.420
You're gonna love it, I promise.

1025
01:05:00.422 --> 01:05:05.184
As long as we're together,
everything is perfect.


1026
01:05:08.315 --> 01:05:12.879
Have you, seen your neighbor,
the one who sent you the ring?


1027
01:05:12.881 --> 01:05:14.477
Sarah?

1028
01:05:14.479 --> 01:05:18.640
Yeah, she... she has a horse
rescue ranch next door.


1029
01:05:18.642 --> 01:05:20.540
Wonderful.

1030
01:05:20.542 --> 01:05:22.904
She depends on funding
to keep it running.


1031
01:05:22.906 --> 01:05:24.602
I'm not sure she got it.

1032
01:05:24.604 --> 01:05:27.367
I offered to help, but
she's too stubborn to let me.


1033
01:05:27.369 --> 01:05:29.365
You're such a good man.

1034
01:05:29.367 --> 01:05:30.699
The bank is threatening
to sell her ranch


1035
01:05:30.701 --> 01:05:32.563
if she doesn't come up with
the money soon.


1036
01:05:32.565 --> 01:05:34.128
What a shame.

1037
01:05:35.163 --> 01:05:36.261
She's a great girl.

1038
01:05:36.263 --> 01:05:38.992
She helped us plan
our whole wedding.


1039
01:05:41.857 --> 01:05:43.588
Hello.

1040
01:05:43.590 --> 01:05:45.819
Yes, the Sun Ranch.

1041
01:05:45.821 --> 01:05:48.517
No, next door.
The yellow house, red barn.


1042
01:05:49.586 --> 01:05:51.615
Rural route 8, Milltown.

1043
01:05:51.617 --> 01:05:54.279
Great.
Thank you.


1044
01:05:54.882 --> 01:05:57.010
What was that all about?

1045
01:05:57.012 --> 01:05:58.410
I just ordered a few things

1046
01:05:58.412 --> 01:06:00.707
to make our wedding
a little more comfortable.


1047
01:06:00.709 --> 01:06:02.907
I told you I'd take care of it.

1048
01:06:02.909 --> 01:06:05.506
You know, I ordered
a cake and flowers...


1049
01:06:05.508 --> 01:06:07.136
And I'm sure you did
a great job.


1050
01:06:07.138 --> 01:06:10.866
But we'll have
our rehearsal dinner,


1051
01:06:10.868 --> 01:06:15.662
then we'll get to Italy,
and back to our real lives.


1052
01:06:17.697 --> 01:06:19.660
All right.

1053
01:06:26.889 --> 01:06:29.086
You know, I love this place.

1054
01:06:29.088 --> 01:06:31.118
I can see that.

1055
01:06:33.117 --> 01:06:34.250
So...

1056
01:06:36.283 --> 01:06:41.111
How long do we actually
need to stay out here for?


1057
01:06:41.113 --> 01:06:42.642
You'll know when you're done.

1058
01:06:44.177 --> 01:06:46.072
Okay, I'm done.

1059
01:06:47.573 --> 01:06:49.271
Hey!

1060
01:06:50.273 --> 01:06:51.302
Catherine!

1061
01:06:51.304 --> 01:06:52.835
Get me outta here!

1062
01:06:52.837 --> 01:06:54.701
Help!

1063
01:06:54.703 --> 01:06:55.800
Get me outta here!

1064
01:06:57.732 --> 01:06:59.662
You all right?

1065
01:06:59.664 --> 01:07:00.596
I suppose.

1066
01:07:00.598 --> 01:07:02.293
I got you.

1067
01:07:02.295 --> 01:07:03.327
Sit down here.

1068
01:07:03.329 --> 01:07:05.092
I can't believe
you made me do that.


1069
01:07:09.224 --> 01:07:11.088
Let's take these off of you.

1070
01:07:17.485 --> 01:07:19.981
Cooper, we got it.

1071
01:07:22.446 --> 01:07:24.212
Let's see...

1072
01:07:30.841 --> 01:07:32.473
Oh, no.

1073
01:07:50.907 --> 01:07:53.977
We're gonna get you better
in no time.


1074
01:07:56.847 --> 01:07:58.014
Good morning!

1075
01:07:58.016 --> 01:08:00.450
Catherine.

1076
01:08:00.452 --> 01:08:02.287
Hi!

1077
01:08:02.289 --> 01:08:04.388
It's so nice to meet you.
I'm a huge fan.


1078
01:08:04.390 --> 01:08:06.190
Oh, sorry.

1079
01:08:06.192 --> 01:08:07.424
Thanks.

1080
01:08:07.428 --> 01:08:10.129
Bradley told me what you're
doing here, rescuing horses.


1081
01:08:10.131 --> 01:08:12.065
I'm... very impressed.

1082
01:08:13.668 --> 01:08:14.866
I love the work.

1083
01:08:14.868 --> 01:08:18.639
It's beautiful here. I can see
why Bradley likes it so much.


1084
01:08:19.741 --> 01:08:24.546
He romanticizes what it would be like
to settle down and raise a family here,


1085
01:08:24.548 --> 01:08:27.750
- ... but that will never happen.
- No?


1086
01:08:27.852 --> 01:08:31.320
Well, once he's back on tour,
jet-setting around the world,


1087
01:08:31.322 --> 01:08:35.292
like he did before,
and never look back.


1088
01:08:35.294 --> 01:08:40.430
He has a gift, something he needs
to share with the world.


1089
01:08:40.432 --> 01:08:42.300
You understand that, right?

1090
01:08:43.333 --> 01:08:45.469
I do.

1091
01:08:45.471 --> 01:08:48.807
He is extraordinary.

1092
01:08:48.809 --> 01:08:51.242
He's very concerned about you.

1093
01:08:51.244 --> 01:08:53.079
He told me about
your financial troubles,


1094
01:08:53.081 --> 01:08:56.549
and I have a friend in the
business, wonderful man.


1095
01:08:56.551 --> 01:08:58.518
There's his name and address.

1096
01:08:58.520 --> 01:09:00.254
He takes in horses
and other animals


1097
01:09:00.256 --> 01:09:02.623
that have retired from
working in TV and films.


1098
01:09:02.625 --> 01:09:07.229
I called him, thinking maybe
he could help, and he can.


1099
01:09:07.231 --> 01:09:10.230
He has room to take your horses
if you need a place to put them.


1100
01:09:10.232 --> 01:09:13.701
In fact, he'd like to talk to you

1101
01:09:13.703 --> 01:09:18.442
about working on his ranch in
California, if you might be interested.


1102
01:09:18.444 --> 01:09:21.077
- That's amazing.
- It's serendipitous.


1103
01:09:21.079 --> 01:09:25.315
I think you should grab the
opportunity and talk to him right away.


1104
01:09:26.217 --> 01:09:27.551
- Okay.
- I know you'd like him.


1105
01:09:27.553 --> 01:09:29.553
Well...

1106
01:09:31.625 --> 01:09:36.526
I hope you'll accept this
as a gift from Bradley and me.


1107
01:09:36.528 --> 01:09:41.767
We want to thank you for working
so hard to put our wedding together.


1108
01:09:43.171 --> 01:09:48.073
I had my assistant book you
on a flight for tomorrow morning.


1109
01:09:50.746 --> 01:09:53.347
This is very sweet of you.

1110
01:09:53.349 --> 01:09:55.683
You'll have to miss the wedding,

1111
01:09:55.685 --> 01:09:59.287
but that's not as important
as saving your horses, is it?


1112
01:09:59.289 --> 01:10:03.291
No.
No, of course not.


1113
01:10:03.293 --> 01:10:05.360
Thank you very much
for doing this.


1114
01:10:05.362 --> 01:10:09.199
A friend of Bradley's
is a friend of mine.


1115
01:10:13.038 --> 01:10:14.037
Catherine!

1116
01:10:15.507 --> 01:10:19.711
- What's your favorite flower?
- Yellow roses.


1117
01:10:19.713 --> 01:10:20.812
Why?

1118
01:10:22.348 --> 01:10:23.683
No reason.

1119
01:10:37.766 --> 01:10:41.769
- Thanks for meeting me here.
- Glad you called.


1120
01:10:41.771 --> 01:10:42.871
You okay?

1121
01:10:42.873 --> 01:10:45.038
Yeah.

1122
01:10:45.040 --> 01:10:49.379
How do people look
when they're... in love?


1123
01:10:49.381 --> 01:10:52.716
And how do they know
they've chosen the right person,


1124
01:10:52.718 --> 01:10:55.553
the one they're supposed to
be with forever?


1125
01:10:57.555 --> 01:10:59.090
Well, the bride gets
this look in her eyes


1126
01:10:59.092 --> 01:11:00.459
when she knows she's doing
the right thing.


1127
01:11:00.461 --> 01:11:02.527
She walks into the church,

1128
01:11:02.529 --> 01:11:05.130
and she looks across
the room at her groom,


1129
01:11:05.132 --> 01:11:07.299
and she's got
these tears in her eyes,


1130
01:11:07.301 --> 01:11:11.937
like she can't see anybody else,
she's lost in the moment.


1131
01:11:12.839 --> 01:11:14.207
And that's it?

1132
01:11:14.209 --> 01:11:18.044
Bradley, the question really is...

1133
01:11:18.046 --> 01:11:19.380
Do you love her?

1134
01:11:19.382 --> 01:11:21.616
Of course.

1135
01:11:21.618 --> 01:11:24.985
I mean, she's done so much
for me, for my career.


1136
01:11:24.987 --> 01:11:26.488
But do you love her?

1137
01:11:26.490 --> 01:11:27.489
Yes.

1138
01:11:27.491 --> 01:11:30.659
You know, I... I love her.

1139
01:11:32.027 --> 01:11:34.163
You sure this is
what you want to do?


1140
01:11:35.499 --> 01:11:38.535
I am, yeah.

1141
01:11:38.537 --> 01:11:40.569
So, I guess I'll see you
at the wedding rehearsal.


1142
01:11:40.571 --> 01:11:42.873
Yeah.

1143
01:11:42.875 --> 01:11:44.242
Okay.

1144
01:11:48.213 --> 01:11:49.280
Thanks.

1145
01:11:49.282 --> 01:11:51.082
Yeah, you bet.

1146
01:12:30.029 --> 01:12:31.562
Okay, let's get started.

1147
01:12:31.564 --> 01:12:34.733
Bradley, hup-two.

1148
01:12:34.736 --> 01:12:38.137
All right, you'll stand
here next to me, faced this way,


1149
01:12:38.139 --> 01:12:40.340
and, Catherine,
when the music starts,


1150
01:12:40.342 --> 01:12:42.308
cross that bridge,
down that row,


1151
01:12:42.310 --> 01:12:45.212
and then you'll walk down
the aisle towards Bradley.


1152
01:12:45.214 --> 01:12:46.981
Got it.

1153
01:12:46.983 --> 01:12:49.350
Okay,
let's try this.


1154
01:14:08.507 --> 01:14:11.044
- Hi, James.
- Hi, Sarah.


1155
01:14:12.614 --> 01:14:16.551
- I'm real sorry about this.
- Yeah. Me too.


1156
01:14:16.553 --> 01:14:18.318
Thank you.

1157
01:14:23.493 --> 01:14:25.727
Hello?

1158
01:14:25.729 --> 01:14:27.929
Sarah?

1159
01:14:27.931 --> 01:14:29.864
I need to talk to you!

1160
01:14:29.866 --> 01:14:31.633
Hello there!

1161
01:14:31.635 --> 01:14:34.137
Aren't you be supposed to be
getting ready for your wedding?


1162
01:14:34.139 --> 01:14:35.972
Where's Sarah?

1163
01:14:35.974 --> 01:14:37.608
She's gone.

1164
01:14:37.610 --> 01:14:39.710
I don't understand.
What do you mean?


1165
01:14:39.712 --> 01:14:41.880
Well, she no longer
owns this ranch.


1166
01:14:41.882 --> 01:14:43.483
What?

1167
01:14:43.484 --> 01:14:44.716
She would never sell her ranch.

1168
01:14:44.718 --> 01:14:46.450
She didn't have a choice.

1169
01:14:46.452 --> 01:14:48.452
She simply didn't have enough
money to make the mortgage.


1170
01:14:48.454 --> 01:14:51.356
The bank had to sell it.
They didn't have a choice.


1171
01:14:51.358 --> 01:14:56.263
I'm taking care of the dogs, but
the horses are getting picked up.


1172
01:14:56.265 --> 01:14:59.066
Well, I'll talk to the people who
bought it, and I'll get it back.


1173
01:14:59.068 --> 01:15:00.267
Who bought the ranch?

1174
01:15:01.069 --> 01:15:02.436
You did.

1175
01:15:04.874 --> 01:15:06.741
Excuse me.

1176
01:15:08.711 --> 01:15:11.214
That's very good.
That's perfect.


1177
01:15:12.715 --> 01:15:14.549
Catherine?

1178
01:15:15.852 --> 01:15:17.219
You can't come in here.

1179
01:15:17.221 --> 01:15:18.454
I need to speak to you.

1180
01:15:18.456 --> 01:15:20.389
You can't see the bride before
the wedding, it's bad luck!


1181
01:15:20.391 --> 01:15:22.894
Did you buy Sarah's ranch?

1182
01:15:24.530 --> 01:15:25.629
Okay.

1183
01:15:25.633 --> 01:15:27.431
Everybody out.

1184
01:15:27.433 --> 01:15:29.333
The groom needs to speak
to the bride.


1185
01:15:35.175 --> 01:15:37.710
Bradley,

1186
01:15:37.712 --> 01:15:40.780
I know how much this place
means to you,


1187
01:15:40.782 --> 01:15:42.348
and I know you want to keep it.

1188
01:15:42.350 --> 01:15:44.751
What's that have to do with
you buying Sarah's ranch?


1189
01:15:44.753 --> 01:15:46.153
We can expand the property,

1190
01:15:46.155 --> 01:15:48.589
build a new house here,
a real house,


1191
01:15:48.590 --> 01:15:52.294
...a house we can come back to.
A house worthy of people like us.


1192
01:15:52.296 --> 01:15:55.331
- People like us?
- You know what I mean.


1193
01:15:58.568 --> 01:16:00.402
Who the heck is that?

1194
01:16:01.405 --> 01:16:03.139
Do you mind?

1195
01:16:05.076 --> 01:16:08.278
- He's with People Magazine.
- Are you kidding me?


1196
01:16:08.280 --> 01:16:10.147
I know you didn't want
the media at our wedding...


1197
01:16:10.149 --> 01:16:11.782
We discussed this!

1198
01:16:11.784 --> 01:16:14.353
He promised he'd be discreet.
You won't even notice him.


1199
01:16:14.355 --> 01:16:16.989
Right.

1200
01:16:16.991 --> 01:16:22.127
I love all the flowers
for the wedding.


1201
01:16:22.129 --> 01:16:26.032
How did you know that yellow
roses were my favorite?


1202
01:16:26.034 --> 01:16:28.536
I didn't.

1203
01:16:28.538 --> 01:16:29.870
Sarah must have known.

1204
01:16:30.837 --> 01:16:33.542
You know, that ranch is her home.

1205
01:16:33.545 --> 01:16:36.209
She's lived there her entire life.

1206
01:16:36.211 --> 01:16:40.997
I think it's so sweet that
you still care about her.


1207
01:16:42.385 --> 01:16:44.120
It's one of the reasons
I love you so much.


1208
01:16:44.122 --> 01:16:46.188
I can't marry you.

1209
01:16:48.392 --> 01:16:49.460
Sorry?

1210
01:16:50.427 --> 01:16:53.230
I can't marry you.

1211
01:16:53.232 --> 01:16:55.966
Of course you can.

1212
01:16:55.968 --> 01:16:58.135
Do you love me?

1213
01:16:58.137 --> 01:17:01.106
- Of course I do.
- Why?


1214
01:17:02.577 --> 01:17:04.709
Because we're perfect
for each other.


1215
01:17:04.711 --> 01:17:07.681
We understand each other.
We want the same things.


1216
01:17:07.683 --> 01:17:10.916
I'm not going to tour
for a while.


1217
01:17:10.918 --> 01:17:14.388
I'm going to live here, play locally,
build a studio, and write music.


1218
01:17:14.390 --> 01:17:15.790
That's so silly.

1219
01:17:15.792 --> 01:17:17.957
Your career is on fire,
you're gaining momentum...


1220
01:17:17.959 --> 01:17:19.159
Catherine.

1221
01:17:20.295 --> 01:17:23.932
I care about you,
I do.


1222
01:17:25.636 --> 01:17:28.369
But it's just not enough.

1223
01:17:30.541 --> 01:17:32.610
I'm sorry.

1224
01:18:29.448 --> 01:18:30.953
Hey, welcome home, Sarah.

1225
01:18:30.955 --> 01:18:35.269
Well, thanks, Sam,
but it's not home anymore.


1226
01:18:35.271 --> 01:18:36.507
I'm just here to pack up.

1227
01:18:36.509 --> 01:18:37.644
Oh, I see.

1228
01:18:37.646 --> 01:18:39.852
Where will you go?

1229
01:18:39.854 --> 01:18:42.195
I don't know.

1230
01:18:42.197 --> 01:18:43.499
Hey, I'm...

1231
01:18:43.501 --> 01:18:45.440
I'm sorry.

1232
01:18:45.442 --> 01:18:48.586
Thanks, Sam.
See you around.


1233
01:19:04.279 --> 01:19:05.548
Hi!

1234
01:19:05.550 --> 01:19:06.585
Hi, guys!

1235
01:19:06.587 --> 01:19:07.688
Hi!

1236
01:19:07.690 --> 01:19:08.793
It's so good to see you!

1237
01:19:09.797 --> 01:19:11.603
I missed you so much!

1238
01:19:12.776 --> 01:19:16.889
Kelly, what are you barking at?
What's going on?


1239
01:19:16.891 --> 01:19:19.031
What's going on, you guys?

1240
01:19:27.061 --> 01:19:28.600
Where are you guys going?

1241
01:19:28.602 --> 01:19:30.441
What got into you?

1242
01:19:30.443 --> 01:19:31.911
Kelly!

1243
01:19:39.575 --> 01:19:41.915
Kelly, whatcha got there?

1244
01:19:43.423 --> 01:19:45.930
What's in there?

1245
01:19:53.896 --> 01:19:54.997
Hi.

1246
01:19:56.571 --> 01:19:59.548
What is going on?

1247
01:19:59.550 --> 01:20:01.087
Did you decide
to have the wedding today?


1248
01:20:01.089 --> 01:20:02.157
Where's Catherine?

1249
01:20:03.430 --> 01:20:04.700
I'm not sure.

1250
01:20:05.203 --> 01:20:08.246
I don't understand.

1251
01:20:08.248 --> 01:20:10.187
Well...

1252
01:20:10.189 --> 01:20:15.272
I was thinking
we could renew our vows.


1253
01:20:15.274 --> 01:20:17.044
We got married
when we were kids.


1254
01:20:17.046 --> 01:20:21.228
I think that was
our one chance at true love.


1255
01:20:23.235 --> 01:20:25.912
True love, huh?

1256
01:20:25.914 --> 01:20:27.183
Well, I don't know.

1257
01:20:27.185 --> 01:20:30.628
That's romantic, not realistic.

1258
01:20:30.630 --> 01:20:31.733
I agree...

1259
01:20:32.972 --> 01:20:35.949
It's rare,

1260
01:20:35.951 --> 01:20:38.325
but I don't want to settle
for less.


1261
01:20:39.864 --> 01:20:41.335
You don't?

1262
01:20:47.995 --> 01:20:50.134
Mint chip,

1263
01:20:50.136 --> 01:20:51.406
blue...

1264
01:20:52.511 --> 01:20:54.818
Horses and dogs...

1265
01:20:55.925 --> 01:20:57.596
White lilies...

1266
01:20:59.504 --> 01:21:01.978
This ranch...

1267
01:21:06.329 --> 01:21:08.938
And these people.

1268
01:21:10.209 --> 01:21:13.420
Those are
all my favorite things.


1269
01:21:16.968 --> 01:21:20.213
I love you with all of my heart,

1270
01:21:20.215 --> 01:21:23.023
and I want to walk through
life leaning against you


1271
01:21:23.025 --> 01:21:25.399
so that neither one of us falls.

1272
01:21:26.436 --> 01:21:27.440
You...

1273
01:21:27.442 --> 01:21:30.517
Are my true love.

1274
01:21:41.659 --> 01:21:42.863
Sarah Standor...

1275
01:21:47.582 --> 01:21:50.457
Will you marry me...

1276
01:21:50.459 --> 01:21:51.896
Again?

1277
01:22:18.362 --> 01:22:23.112
And do you, Sarah, promise to love
Bradley in sickness and in health,


1278
01:22:23.114 --> 01:22:25.454
forever and ever?

1279
01:22:26.759 --> 01:22:29.334
I do.

1280
01:22:29.336 --> 01:22:31.442
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.


1281
01:22:31.444 --> 01:22:33.852
You may kiss the bride.